{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17605962","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17605962"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T13:06:05+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T13:06:05+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15882"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15882","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15882"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.67,0,0.04,0.21,0.08]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8573"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72047"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8573","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8573"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15882"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57517"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4934"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4940"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"8581"},{"type":"tags","id":"10484"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20555"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20556"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72047","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/72047"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EDuring human fertilisation, a sperm cell must penetrate several barriers to reach the oocyte. The first major barrier is the zona pellucida, a glycoprotein layer surrounding the oocyte.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the immediate cellular response when a sperm binds to the zona pellucida?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Calcium influx triggers acrosomal enzyme release","Formation of the male pronucleus begins","Fusion with oocyte membrane occurs","Cortical granules release their contents","Flagellar movement increases"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EWhen a sperm binds to specific glycoproteins in the zona pellucida, it triggers a \u003Cstrong\u003Ecalcium influx that causes acrosomal enzyme release\u003C/strong\u003E. These enzymes digest a path through the zona pellucida to allow sperm penetration.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other events occur later in the fertilisation sequence:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFormation of the male pronucleus\u003C/strong\u003E can only begin after the sperm has entered the oocyte cytoplasm\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFusion with oocyte membrane\u003C/strong\u003E requires prior penetration through the zona pellucida\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECortical granules release their contents\u003C/strong\u003E only after sperm-egg fusion, preventing polyspermy\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EIncreased \u003Cstrong\u003Eflagellar movement\u003C/strong\u003E alone cannot penetrate the zona without prior enzymatic digestion\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe acrosome reaction is essential for successful fertilisation as it enables the sperm to breach the zona pellucida barrier.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The acrosome reaction is triggered by calcium influx when sperm binds to the zona pellucida, releasing enzymes that digest a path through the zona","The sequence of fertilisation events is: binding, acrosome reaction, zona penetration, membrane fusion, cortical reaction"],"references":["Reid AT, Redgrove K, Aitken RJ, Nixon B. Cellular mechanisms regulating sperm-zona pellucida interaction. Asian J Androl. 2011 Jan;13(1):88-96. doi: 10.1038/aja.2010.74. Epub 2010 Nov 1. PMID: 21042304; PMCID: PMC3739399.","Leung ETY, Lee BKM, Lee CL, Tian X, Lam KKW, Li RHW, Ng EHY, Yeung WSB, Ou JP, Chiu PCN. The role of spermatozoa-zona pellucida interaction in selecting fertilization-competent spermatozoa in humans. Front Endocrinol (Lausanne). 2023 Mar 20;14:1135973. doi: 10.3389/fendo.2023.1135973. PMID: 37020592; PMCID: PMC10067631.","Evans, T. J., \u0026 Ganjam, V. K. (2017). Reproductive anatomy and physiology. In Reproductive and Developmental Toxicology (pp. 7-37). Academic Press.","Ansell, I. D. (2012). Atlas of male reproductive pathology (Vol. 10). Springer Science \u0026 Business Media.","Arulkumaran, S., Ledger, W., Denny, L., \u0026 Doumouchtsis, S. (Eds.). (2019). Oxford Textbook of Obstetrics and Gynaecology. Oxford University Press"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57517"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15882"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57517","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/57517"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-20T21:41:19+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-20T21:42:14+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8573"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72047"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"